                <note>
<p>OMEN</p>
<p>auguria are natural events which posses a meaning for those only who are skilful in the interpretation of signs.</p>
<p>auspicia are natural events which can be interpreted by specialists whose official duty it is to intepret such signs.</p>
<p>prodigia, ostentum, portenta and monstra are appearances out of the ordinary course the ordinary course of nature, which sgtrike the common people and only receive a more exact interpretation from the specialist.</p>
<p>prodigium refers to an appearance which is replete with meaning and pregnant with consequences.</p>
<p>monstrum refers to a sign which is striking through its ugliness and/or unnatural.</p>
<p>ostentum is a sign which excites wonder by its overwhelming size or scale.</p>
<p>omina are signs which any person to whom they occur can interpret for himjself without assistance.</p>
                </note>
